**Decision: Redis Streams.** The conclusion is driven by operational reality: a 6-person team with no infra engineer that already runs Redis in production cannot absorb the JVM cluster tax of Kafka at this scale. Every constraint (2-week timeline, modest budget, Redis familiarity, 500 req/s peak) points the same way. The exactly-once gap for billing events is closed by idempotent consumers — a well-understood pattern that's simpler to maintain than Kafka's transactional protocol.

The ADR includes concrete reopening conditions (50k req/s sustained or >7 day retention requirements) and a migration path so this choice doesn't become a permanent constraint.
